text.section:
The surety bond shall:
Run to the Commissioner and be for the benefit of any mortgage loan borrower who has been damaged by a violation committed by a licensee of any law or regulation governing the activities of mortgage lenders;
Be issued by a surety company authorized to do business in the State;
Be conditioned that the applicant shall comply with all Maryland laws regulating the activities of mortgage lenders and mortgage loan lending; and
Be approved by the Commissioner.
